name: 埃米亚·蒂吉
introduction: EaeMya ThynGi is a Burmese-Canadian actor/singer, based in Vancouver, BC. She fell in love with theatre from a young age and began to perform in Riverside's River's Edge musical theatre program throughout her high school years. From there, ThynGi went on to portray the lead role of "Sophie Sheridan" in the musical Mamma Mia with Broadway Dance Canada. Transitioning to the film and television industry in 2021, she can be seen in the upcoming release of shows such as Motherland: Fort Salem and The Bad Seed Returns.
